Question40
40. Write a PHP script to remove all characters from a string except a-z A-Z 0-9 or " " using an array.
ANSWER
<?php
// Original string with special characters
$original = "Hello, World! This #1 is @PHP-Test_2025.";
// Step 1: Split string into characters (array)
$chars = str_split($original);
// Step 2: Create an array to hold allowed characters
$filtered = [];

// Step 3: Loop through each character
foreach ($chars as $char) {
    if (ctype_alnum($char) || $char === ' ') {
        $filtered[] = $char; // Keep only letters, digits, and space
    }
}
// Step 4: Join filtered characters back into a string
$cleaned = implode('', $filtered);
// Output
echo "Original: $original\n";
echo "Cleaned: $cleaned\n";
?>

OUTPUT
Original: Hello, World! This #1 is @PHP-Test_2025.
Cleaned: Hello World This 1 is PHPTest2025
